data.description:
in this kata you will make class `Language` that can define immutable/mutable variable, have method that can do like if / else / else if, have method that can do like switch satement,
have method that can do for loop and while loop, and can delete the variable.

example use:
```javascript
const lang = new Language()

// create mutable variable with value 1
lang.let.a(1)
lang.a = 5 // a change from 1 to 5

// create immutable variable with value 'freeze'
lang.const.b('cold')
lang.b = 'hot' // b still 'cold' not cahnged to 'hot'

// cannot redefine the existing variable
lang.const.b('new')

// can create many variable in one line
lang.let.c(true).d('value').e({name: 'user'})
lang.const.f([0,2,4,6]).g(/[a-z]+/)

// if
lang.if(()=> lang.a === 5)
       .do(()=> lang.d = 'change')

// if else
lang.if(/*condition*/)
       .do(/*some function*/)
    .else(()=> lang.d = 'aiueo')

// if else elseIf
lang.if(/*condition*/)
       .do(/*some function*/)
    .elseIf(/*condition*/)
       .do(/*some function*/)
    .else(/*some function*/)

// switch
lang.const.rank('C')
lang.switch(lang.rank, (_case, _default) => {
  _case('A', ()=> console.log('amazing'))
  _case('B', ()=> console.log('good'))
  _case('C', ()=> console.log('not bad'))
  _default(()=> console.log('nah'))
})

// for
lang.for(()=> lang.let.i(0), 
         ()=> lang.i < 10, 
         ()=> lang.i++,
         ()=> {
  console.log(lang.i)
})

// while
lang.let.n(10)
lang.while(()=> lang.n > 0, ()=> {
  console.log(lang.n)
})

// can delete variable
lang.delete.a

// multiple delete in one line
// variable 'b' cannot deleted because 'b' is immutable
lang.delete.b.c.d

// the key is customizable

const l = new Language({
  mutableVarKey: 'create',// default 'let'
  immutableVarKey: 'define', // default 'const'
  ifKey: 'is', // default 'if'
  doKey: 'execute', // default 'do'
  elseKey: 'ifNotDo', // default 'else'
  elseIfKey: 'or', // default 'elseIf'
  switchKey: 'test', // default 'switch'
  forKey: 'runs', // default 'for'
  whileKey: 'repeatIf', // default 'while'
  deleteKey: 'remove', // default 'delete'
})

l.create.a(20).b('hi').c(false)
l.define.x({}).y(5.25).z([0])
```
# note<br>
- the `_case` and `_default` the name can be replaced with another
